327
00:31:48.949 --> 00:31:51.452
INSURANCE POLICY

328
00:31:56.290 --> 00:32:01.337
POLICYHOLDER: CHA WOO-SEOK
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH

329
00:32:03.922 --> 00:32:06.425
If we set a trap.
he'll walk right into it.

330
00:32:09.053 --> 00:32:11.722
{\an8}MAIN COVERAGE:
NATURAL DEATH. GENERAL INJURY

331
00:32:17.144 --> 00:32:18.187
Do I look like a joke?

332
00:32:19.438 --> 00:32:20.939
Why does everyone treat me as they wish?

333
00:32:22.524 --> 00:32:23.442
Seol-ah.

334
00:32:23.942 --> 00:32:25.569
You need to think about this rationally.

335
00:32:25.653 --> 00:32:27.488
The real culprit will show up
if we do this.

336
00:32:28.280 --> 00:32:31.241
Do you have any idea
how cruel this is to me?

337
00:32:32.117 --> 00:32:33.035
Seol-ah.

338
00:32:33.118 --> 00:32:35.537
What if I just use you and walk away?

339
00:32:37.956 --> 00:32:39.375
What if you really die?

340
00:32:45.631 --> 00:32:46.590
It doesn't matter.

341
00:32:48.717 --> 00:32:49.802
I don't care.

342
00:32:58.185 --> 00:32:59.353
Go ahead and use me.

343
00:33:03.023 --> 00:33:05.275
Have you ever lived with the guilt
of someone dying

344
00:33:05.359 --> 00:33:07.194
because of you?

345
00:33:08.696 --> 00:33:10.406
Do you know how painful that is?

346
00:33:15.411 --> 00:33:16.328
I do.

347
00:33:18.622 --> 00:33:20.124
I lost the only family I had.

348
00:33:29.049 --> 00:33:30.300
After our parents divorcedâ€¦

349
00:33:32.261 --> 00:33:33.887
our grandmother raised us.

350
00:33:36.807 --> 00:33:38.350
After our grandmother passed away.

351
00:33:39.977 --> 00:33:41.103
it was just the two of us.

352
00:33:52.781 --> 00:33:56.368
The first thing I did when you told me
you were going to be a cop

353
00:33:56.452 --> 00:33:58.996
was to get a first aid kit.

354
00:34:01.623 --> 00:34:03.459
Please don't get hurt.

355
00:34:04.209 --> 00:34:07.880
I was supposed to be
Woo-hee's mom. dad. and older brother.

356
00:34:09.214 --> 00:34:10.716
but she took care of me instead.

357
00:34:11.925 --> 00:34:13.093
She was always strong.

358
00:34:13.177 --> 00:34:14.011
Even more so than me.

359
00:34:17.222 --> 00:34:18.265
After I became a cop.

360
00:34:20.142 --> 00:34:22.269
I spent day and night chasing criminals.

361
00:34:24.688 --> 00:34:26.482
But I couldn't protect my own family.

362
00:34:36.867 --> 00:34:39.495
If only I had just checked on her again.
I wouldn't have lost her that way.

363
00:34:47.336 --> 00:34:50.130
After I lost her. I threw myself
into solving cases like a madman.

364
00:34:50.839 --> 00:34:52.841
I thought working myself to death
and catching criminals

365
00:34:53.759 --> 00:34:55.594
would make me feel better.

366
00:34:57.763 --> 00:34:58.931
But it didn't.

367
00:35:00.349 --> 00:35:01.433
I realizedâ€¦

368
00:35:03.477 --> 00:35:05.646
that no matter who I saved.
this guilt wouldn't go away.

369
00:35:07.648 --> 00:35:09.149
It wasn't your fault.

370
00:35:10.442 --> 00:35:11.318
No.

371
00:35:12.778 --> 00:35:14.071
It was my fault.

372
00:35:17.282 --> 00:35:18.826
I couldn't protect my sister.

373
00:35:25.666 --> 00:35:27.960
We're trapped in the same prison.

374
00:35:29.378 --> 00:35:31.004
living each dayâ€¦

375
00:35:32.923 --> 00:35:34.341
with the people we couldn't protect.

376
00:35:49.481 --> 00:35:51.942
NEULSAEM GENERAL HOSPITAL

377
00:36:20.178 --> 00:36:21.179
You got me.

378
00:36:21.263 --> 00:36:22.848
I thought I was hiding it well.

379
00:36:23.557 --> 00:36:25.976
You need a good eye to be an auctioneer.

380
00:36:29.730 --> 00:36:31.231
Did you get hurt in the accident?

381
00:36:33.984 --> 00:36:34.902
Yes.

382
00:36:40.866 --> 00:36:41.950
From now onâ€¦

383
00:36:45.370 --> 00:36:46.496
please don't get hurt.

384
00:37:31.583 --> 00:37:32.793
AHN YOUNG-SOO

385
