431
00:44:44.391 --> 00:44:46.851
What's Paek Jun-beom trying to hide?

432
00:44:47.894 --> 00:44:49.813
Are you sure he was behind this?

433
00:44:50.980 --> 00:44:51.898
Why would he?

434
00:44:54.234 --> 00:44:56.820
You know something important. don't you?

435
00:44:57.445 --> 00:44:59.906
Su-ho kept saying he wanted to die

436
00:44:59.989 --> 00:45:01.324
after his girlfriend broke up with him.

437
00:45:01.866 --> 00:45:03.535
and he even ignored the air raid warning.

438
00:45:04.828 --> 00:45:06.788
The way I see it.
he basically committed suicide.

439
00:45:10.792 --> 00:45:13.920
And Jun-beom got injured
trying to save Su-ho.

440
00:45:19.092 --> 00:45:22.387
YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

441
00:46:29.329 --> 00:46:31.915
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">I found out where Lee Su-ho</font></i>
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">was laid to rest.</font></i>

442
00:46:33.541 --> 00:46:35.210
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">If it's too much for you to handle.</font></i>
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">I'll come with you.</font></i>

443
00:47:06.866 --> 00:47:09.202
{\an8}THE LATE LEE SU-HO
MAY 7. 1991 - JUNE 14. 2018

444
00:47:19.963 --> 00:47:21.548
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">He was an orphan with no family.</font></i>

445
00:47:22.423 --> 00:47:24.092
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">so I placed his ashes in a columbarium.</font></i>

446
00:47:40.567 --> 00:47:41.401
I think

447
00:47:42.527 --> 00:47:44.571
Mr. Paek wanted me to come here.

448
00:47:49.117 --> 00:47:50.159
To be honest.

449
00:47:50.660 --> 00:47:53.705
I knew that Su-ho

