483
00:50:05.878 --> 00:50:08.464
a 34-year-old man who had served time
for assault resulting in death.

484
00:50:08.548 --> 00:50:10.633
He's a former special forces NCO

485
00:50:11.217 --> 00:50:13.553
with service experience in Syria.

486
00:50:13.636 --> 00:50:16.180
He was in Syria with Paek Jun-beom. huh?

487
00:50:16.264 --> 00:50:18.891
That means Paek Jun-beom calls the shots.
and Kim Sung-hae just follows.

488
00:50:18.975 --> 00:50:20.685
But as of right now.

489
00:50:20.768 --> 00:50:23.521
his trips to the office building
aren't enough to tie him to the case

490
00:50:23.604 --> 00:50:25.523
unless a search and seizure is conducted.

491
00:50:25.606 --> 00:50:26.524
Let's catch them.

492
00:50:27.233 --> 00:50:29.944
Start with Kim Sung-hae.
Put out an APB for attempted murder.

493
00:50:31.154 --> 00:50:32.029
Yes. sir.

494
00:51:03.561 --> 00:51:04.395
Hello. Ms. Han.

495
00:51:04.479 --> 00:51:05.730
Allow me to escort you
to the CEO's office.

496
00:51:26.834 --> 00:51:28.252
Mr. Paek will be here soon.

497
00:51:28.336 --> 00:51:30.463
Please have a seat and wait for a moment.

498
00:51:30.546 --> 00:51:32.006
Sure thing.

499
00:51:37.845 --> 00:51:39.096
YOUR HOME
CEO PAEK JUN-BEOM

500
00:51:51.567 --> 00:51:52.485
DELETINGâ€¦
SELECTED FILES: 30

501
00:51:52.568 --> 00:51:53.986
YOUR HOME INTEGRATED CONTROL CENTER
CCTV SYSTEM

502
00:51:54.070 --> 00:51:55.196
As instructed.

503
00:51:55.279 --> 00:51:58.032
we're deleting all the footage
tracking your movements. sir.

504
00:51:58.115 --> 00:52:00.785
Delete the recent footage
of the parking lot entrance too.

505
00:52:01.369 --> 00:52:02.495
All of it. sir?

506
00:52:04.372 --> 00:52:05.581
Understood.

507
00:52:06.999 --> 00:52:10.378
DELETINGâ€¦
SELECTED FILES: 382

508
00:52:16.133 --> 00:52:18.719
The barrier gate camera
would've caught 4549

509
00:52:18.803 --> 00:52:21.347
as it entered and left
the office building.

510
00:52:22.473 --> 00:52:23.516
THANK YOU
GOODBYE

511
00:52:29.480 --> 00:52:30.690
Take a look at this. sir.

512
00:52:30.773 --> 00:52:34.235
This system automatically records
and recognizes license plates.

513
00:52:34.318 --> 00:52:36.445
but it also records who's inside the car.

514
00:52:37.613 --> 00:52:38.656
But the thing is.

515
00:52:38.739 --> 00:52:42.159
nobody thinks this is important.
so the security is pathetic.

516
00:52:42.243 --> 00:52:44.287
They might as well roll out a welcome mat.

517
00:52:44.370 --> 00:52:45.830
See? I'm in already.

518
00:52:45.913 --> 00:52:47.707
Grab all the files. then.

519
00:52:47.790 --> 00:52:49.083
Yes. sir.

520
00:52:50.877 --> 00:52:52.295
Right on it.

521
00:52:57.592 --> 00:52:58.426
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

522
00:52:58.509 --> 00:52:59.427
Hold on.

523
00:52:59.927 --> 00:53:02.722
These bastards are deleting
all the files in real time.

524
00:53:03.806 --> 00:53:06.267
They must've caught on
that we know about the ghost car.

525
00:53:07.018 --> 00:53:09.270
Paek Jun-beom isn't showing up
because he's busy deleting these files.

526
00:53:33.210 --> 00:53:35.129
HAN SEOL-AH

527
00:53:39.634 --> 00:53:41.928
I'm sorry. Something came up.

528
00:53:42.011 --> 00:53:43.387
Have you been waiting long?

529
00:53:43.471 --> 00:53:45.306
No. I just got here.

530
00:53:45.806 --> 00:53:46.766
Please sit.

531
00:53:51.520 --> 00:53:52.355
Here.

532
00:54:03.491 --> 00:54:05.034
YOU ARE CORDIALLY INVITED TO ROYAL AUCTION
KOREA'S PREMIER FINE ART AUCTION HOUSE

533
00:54:06.911 --> 00:54:07.828
An invitation?

534
00:54:08.788 --> 00:54:12.583
It's for a preview event
for our VVIP clients.

535
00:54:12.667 --> 00:54:16.545
and it'll also be the first public showing
of the Stiller.

536
00:54:17.129 --> 00:54:18.547
Then I should attend.

537
00:54:18.631 --> 00:54:19.966
That piece meant a great deal to me.

538
00:54:22.009 --> 00:54:24.553
Everyone has been wondering
who owned the Stiller.

539
00:54:26.180 --> 00:54:29.684
Are you okay with your identity
being revealed?

540
00:54:36.440 --> 00:54:37.942
I liked having an air of mystery.

541
00:54:38.025 --> 00:54:39.986
but I guess that's over now.
thanks to you.

542
00:54:42.113 --> 00:54:43.322
By the way.

543
00:54:44.407 --> 00:54:45.908
about <i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">An Orphan from Syriaâ€¦</font></i>

544
00:54:51.580 --> 00:54:54.583
That piece clearly means a lot to you.

545
00:54:57.128 --> 00:55:00.089
May I ask why you consigned it to me?

546
00:55:10.433 --> 00:55:13.102
I wanted to show more of myself.

547
00:55:15.021 --> 00:55:16.981
The piece feels like the real me
without a mask.

548
00:55:19.191 --> 00:55:21.777
You see. I grew up with nothing.

549
00:55:21.861 --> 00:55:24.280
like an orphaned child in wartime.

550
00:55:25.239 --> 00:55:26.240
To be honest.

551
00:55:27.283 --> 00:55:29.076
it still feels strange

552
00:55:30.411 --> 00:55:31.412
to be where I am right now.

553
00:55:35.458 --> 00:55:37.043
You need a thick mask

554
00:55:37.543 --> 00:55:40.713
to pretend like nothing's wrong.

555
00:55:47.762 --> 00:55:48.929
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

556
00:55:51.265 --> 00:55:53.059
THIS FILE HAS BEEN DELETED

557
00:56:00.316 --> 00:56:01.150
Found it.

558
00:56:01.233 --> 00:56:05.279
{\an8}Man. I found it by the skin of my teeth.

559
00:56:06.030 --> 00:56:08.574
Another few seconds.
and this file would've been gone.

560
00:56:08.657 --> 00:56:10.159
It's Paek Jun-beom.

561
00:56:10.242 --> 00:56:12.286
So this is why he deleted everything.

562
00:56:12.369 --> 00:56:14.872
This bastard is so calculating.

563
00:56:14.955 --> 00:56:16.665
He's one scary man.

564
00:56:16.749 --> 00:56:18.375
What a bastard.

565
00:56:21.921 --> 00:56:23.297
Why don't youâ€¦

566
00:56:24.924 --> 00:56:27.176
take off that mask now?

567
00:56:32.932 --> 00:56:33.974
Who exactly are you?

568
00:56:35.309 --> 00:56:37.061
Why did you approach me

569
00:56:37.144 --> 00:56:39.188
when you knew Su-ho?

570
00:57:04.421 --> 00:57:07.133
Do you think I blame youâ€¦

571
00:57:09.218 --> 00:57:10.553
for Su-ho's death?

572
00:57:17.768 --> 00:57:19.019
Or do you thinkâ€¦

573
00:57:29.321 --> 00:57:31.198
I'm getting revenge for him?

574
00:57:41.333 --> 00:57:42.835
-She's in danger.
-What?

575
00:57:43.586 --> 00:57:44.545
Sir!

576
00:58:04.023 --> 00:58:07.234
{\an8}SPECIAL THANKS TO KIM DONGJUN
FOR HIS APPEARANCE

577
00:58:30.633 --> 00:58:32.176
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">It doesn't make sense.</font></i>

578
00:58:32.259 --> 00:58:34.428
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">Even if this is a revenge</font></i>
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">on Su-ho's behalf.</font></i>

579
00:58:34.511 --> 00:58:36.263
{\an8}it's way too extreme.

580
00:58:36.764 --> 00:58:38.766
{\an8}It's similar to my sister's accident.

581
00:58:38.849 --> 00:58:42.436
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">Criminals rely on familiar tactics</font></i>
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">and tend to repeat what's worked before.</font></i>

582
00:58:42.519 --> 00:58:45.940
{\an8}I'm also chasing the person
who ruined my life.

583
00:58:46.023 --> 00:58:47.691
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">Let's uncover</font></i>

584
00:58:48.234 --> 00:58:50.819
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">the hidden truth together.</font></i>

585
00:58:50.903 --> 00:58:54.448
{\an8}Isn't there something
you really want to say to me?

586
00:58:54.907 --> 00:58:57.993
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">Now we can finally find out</font></i>
<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">what Paek Jun-beom was trying to hide.</font></i>

587
00:58:58.077 --> 00:58:59.161
{\an8}Let go of me!

588
00:58:59.245 --> 00:59:01.080
{\an8}<i><font face="sansSerif" color="white">It's finally come to this.</font></i>

589
00:59:02.581 --> 00:59:04.583
{\an8}Subtitle: Jenny Kim
